input: Anne is quiet. Anne is smart. Bob is green. Bob is kind. Bob is nice. Bob is smart. Erin is round. Erin is not smart. Gary is not green. Gary is kind. Gary is round. If someone is nice and young then they are kind. If Gary is smart and Gary is nice then Gary is quiet. If someone is young then they are round. If Anne is round then Anne is nice. If someone is quiet then they are young. If Gary is young then Gary is not nice. If someone is kind and smart then they are green. Question: Anne is green.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Anne : obj
constant Bob : obj
constant Erin : obj
constant Gary : obj

constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant Smart : obj → Prop
constant Green : obj → Prop
constant Kind : obj → Prop
constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Round : obj → Prop
constant Young : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Quiet Anne
axiom T2 : Smart Anne
axiom T3 : Green Bob
axiom T4 : Kind Bob
axiom T5 : Nice Bob
axiom T6 : Smart Bob
axiom T7 : Round Erin
axiom T8 : ¬ Smart Erin
axiom T9 : ¬ Green Gary
axiom T10 : Kind Gary
axiom T11 : Round Gary

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x ∧ Young x → Kind x
axiom R2 : Smart Gary ∧ Nice Gary → Quiet Gary
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Young x → Round x
axiom R4 : Round Anne → Nice Anne
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x → Young x
axiom R6 : Young Gary → ¬ Nice Gary
axiom R7 : ∀ x : obj, Kind x ∧ Smart x → Green x

theorem anne_is_green : Green Anne :=
begin
  apply R7,
  split,
  apply R1,
  split,
  apply R4,
  apply R3,
  apply R5,
  exact T1,
  exact T2,
end

-- The answer is True
